22/12/2006
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- The European Commission (EC) announced on Thursday (December 21st) plans to recruit some 1,058 employees from Bulgaria and Romania in 2007.
Some 698 posts are envisioned for Romania and 360 posts for Bulgaria, according to quotas determined on the basis of population, the number of votes in the European Council and the number of their members in the European Parliament.
Following a five-year transition period, normal EU recruitment procedures will go into effect.
(Dnevnik - 22/12/06;
Novinite.com - 21/12/06)
